title: "Maxxxine"
rating: 5.0
review {
  direction {
    director {
      name: "Ti West"
    }
    rating: "Pretty Bad"
    comments: "The direction on a macroscale is decent as they show the dichotomy of 1980s LA with the glamour of Hollywood and the fear of the Night Stalker, but he does a bad job with a bigger budget and the more responsibilities that come with it; the direction on a microscale is bad as a lot of the performances feel phoned in and the interpersonal scenes do not feel like they move the story at all; the storytelling is not good as it does not feel like the movie is moving towards anything, and this is only further supported in the climax; they build tension decently well through the visions, but not as good as the first two movies"
  }
