  pacing: "Pacing falters from the plot being very mismanaged"
  climax: "Climax is poorly executed as it feels like it is completely disjoint from the rest of the movie (and there are some moments that are just so funny at how they even got included); the movie should have just ended at the climax because the exposition was actually pointless"
  tone: "Tone is very 1980s, mixed with slasher elements"
  final_notes: "This is a strong step back from the previous two movies as this movie feels more like a spiritual successor rather than a sequel to \"X\" ; the biggest issue from this movie is conflict as it genuinely ruins how the rest of the movie turns out; all these issues stem from the fact that it has an increased budget and that removed the charm these movies had"
  overall: "Overall, a substantial step back from the previous two movies in the \'X\' trilogy, as all of its issues stem from the fact that an increased budget made this movie lose its charm"
